BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 23 Apr--On Saturday, just before midnight, 
the first national congress of the Freedom Union, a party that 
has been formed as a result of the merger of the Democratic 
Union [UD] and the Liberal Democratic Congress [KLD], elected 
Tadeusz Mazowiecki the chairman of the new party. KLD Chairman 
Donald Tusk has been elected deputy chairman. 
  Mazowiecki received 623 votes, with 57 votes against, and 
Tusk received 633 votes, with 48 against. The election took 
place in accordance with agreements reached earlier by the UD 
and KLD Presidiums. 

